00:08:51.560 --> 00:08:53.840 align:middle line:84%
you start investigating
these things, right?

00:08:53.840 --> 00:08:55.932 align:middle line:84%
And you see there's
really evidence for this.

00:08:55.932 --> 00:08:57.890 align:middle line:84%
And what's more, no one's
telling you about it.

00:08:57.890 --> 00:08:59.473 align:middle line:84%
And that was true
with remote viewing.

00:08:59.473 --> 00:09:01.040 align:middle line:84%
I thought, how
could this be real

00:09:01.040 --> 00:09:02.863 align:middle line:84%
that you could take
an average person,

00:09:02.863 --> 00:09:04.280 align:middle line:84%
put them in a class
for a few days

00:09:04.280 --> 00:09:08.090 align:middle line:84%
and they can start getting good
results describing target sites

00:09:08.090 --> 00:09:10.550 align:middle line:84%
that they haven't seen
yet, and yet no one's

00:09:10.550 --> 00:09:12.880 align:middle line:84%
told me about this in
27 years of education?

00:09:12.880 --> 00:09:13.680 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Exactly.

00:09:13.680 --> 00:09:14.210 align:middle line:90%
>>HEIN: Right.

00:09:14.210 --> 00:09:16.460 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What do you think
of the government's program

00:09:16.460 --> 00:09:17.720 align:middle line:90%
investigating remote viewing?

00:09:17.720 --> 00:09:19.260 align:middle line:84%
I mean, Ed Dames was
one of those members.

00:09:19.260 --> 00:09:20.927 align:middle line:84%
>>HEIN: Yeah, he was,
he was part of it.

00:09:20.927 --> 00:09:23.510 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Russell Targ, Ingo
Swann and all those people.

00:09:23.510 --> 00:09:25.445 align:middle line:84%
What do you think
of that program?

00:09:25.445 --> 00:09:27.320 align:middle line:84%
>>HEIN: They, George,
they started doing this

00:09:27.320 --> 00:09:29.008 align:middle line:90%
because they were afraid.

00:09:29.008 --> 00:09:30.050 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Of the Russians.

00:09:30.050 --> 00:09:30.590 align:middle line:90%
>>HEIN: Exactly right.

00:09:30.590 --> 00:09:31.370 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: The Soviets.

00:09:31.370 --> 00:09:32.360 align:middle line:90%
>>HEIN: Exactly right.

00:09:32.360 --> 00:09:35.870 align:middle line:10%
They did it out of fear that
the other, our adversaries

00:09:35.870 --> 00:09:38.835 align:middle line:10%
were going to gain on
us in this area of.

00:09:38.835 --> 00:09:40.710 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: If we don't do
it, they will, right?

00:09:40.710 --> 00:09:41.510 align:middle line:90%
>>HEIN: Yes.

00:09:41.510 --> 00:09:43.340 align:middle line:84%
Psychotronic weapons,
as they called it.

00:09:43.340 --> 00:09:44.840 align:middle line:84%
There's been a lot
of documents that

00:09:44.840 --> 00:09:47.540 align:middle line:84%
have come forth recently
showing that our intelligence

00:09:47.540 --> 00:09:51.840 align:middle line:84%
agencies were initially
saw this as a threat, not

00:09:51.840 --> 00:09:52.640 align:middle line:90%
an opportunity.

00:09:52.640 --> 00:09:52.960 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Exactly.

00:09:52.960 --> 00:09:54.940 align:middle line:84%
>>HEIN: It's a threat,
the Russians, the Chinese.

00:09:54.940 --> 00:09:57.080 align:middle line:10%
And those countries had very
advanced programs in this.

00:09:57.080 --> 00:09:58.030 align:middle line:90%
They took it seriously.

00:09:58.030 --> 00:09:59.420 align:middle line:84%
They didn't have the
skepticism that we

00:09:59.420 --> 00:10:00.440 align:middle line:90%
do in the United States.

00:10:00.440 --> 00:10:02.880 align:middle line:84%
And so they eventually,
our government said, well,

00:10:02.880 --> 00:10:04.610 align:middle line:84%
if they have it, we
have to investigate.

00:10:04.610 --> 00:10:07.170 align:middle line:84%
And they took people like Ingo
Swann, Pat Price and others.

00:10:07.170 --> 00:10:08.210 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: The best of the best.

00:10:08.210 --> 00:10:09.010 align:middle line:90%
>>HEIN: Yeah.

00:10:09.010 --> 00:10:11.870 align:middle line:84%
And they said, it's really real,
and what can we do with it?

00:10:11.870 --> 00:10:13.820 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Why did they stop it?

00:10:13.820 --> 00:10:14.863 align:middle line:90%
Or did they?

00:10:14.863 --> 00:10:15.780 align:middle line:90%
>>HEIN: Good question.

00:10:15.780 --> 00:10:17.810 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I ask that to
people like Ed Dames,

00:10:17.810 --> 00:10:21.030 align:middle line:90%
and he said it stopped.

00:10:21.030 --> 00:10:22.560 align:middle line:84%
And I said, how
do you know that?

00:10:22.560 --> 00:10:24.630 align:middle line:84%
He said, because they're
not using us anymore,

00:10:24.630 --> 00:10:26.460 align:middle line:84%
and we were the
best of the best.

00:10:26.460 --> 00:10:30.310 align:middle line:84%
Well, that makes a little
sense, but why did they stop?

00:10:30.310 --> 00:10:32.260 align:middle line:84%
>>HEIN: Allegedly,
they stopped because it

00:10:32.260 --> 00:10:34.930 align:middle line:84%
needed funding that you
have to go to Congress.

00:10:34.930 --> 00:10:36.177 align:middle line:90%
There was the giggle factor.

00:10:36.177 --> 00:10:38.260 align:middle line:84%
It was a time when they
were doing a lot of budget

00:10:38.260 --> 00:10:39.280 align:middle line:90%
cutting in the mid '90s.

00:10:39.280 --> 00:10:40.420 align:middle line:84%
But we don't know if
it really stopped.

00:10:40.420 --> 00:10:42.253 align:middle line:84%
It could have been
passed to other programs,

00:10:42.253 --> 00:10:44.630 align:middle line:84%
just like we've heard the
AATIP program that studied UFOs

00:10:44.630 --> 00:10:46.990 align:middle line:84%
in the Pentagon, it could be
shifted to another program,

00:10:46.990 --> 00:10:49.030 align:middle line:84%
changed the name, no
one hears about it.

00:10:49.030 --> 00:10:51.550 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You're also an
expert in crop circles, crop

00:10:51.550 --> 00:10:52.990 align:middle line:90%
formations.

00:10:52.990 --> 00:10:55.930 align:middle line:90%
What on Earth are these things?

00:10:55.930 --> 00:10:58.180 align:middle line:90%
How do we explain these?

00:10:58.180 --> 00:11:02.940 align:middle line:84%
I mean, yes, if you have one
done by a group of people

00:11:02.940 --> 00:11:06.830 align:middle line:84%
and it takes them 20 hours to
make, I can understand that.

00:11:06.830 --> 00:11:09.910 align:middle line:84%
But if there's just one
that you can't explain,

00:11:09.910 --> 00:11:12.200 align:middle line:90%
that's the story of the century.

00:11:12.200 --> 00:11:13.420 align:middle line:90%
What are they?

00:11:13.420 --> 00:11:15.670 align:middle line:84%
>>HEIN: Well, George,
I got into crop circles

00:11:15.670 --> 00:11:16.732 align:middle line:90%
from remote viewing.

00:11:16.732 --> 00:11:18.940 align:middle line:84%
And by the way, I call it
actually, resonant viewing.

00:11:18.940 --> 00:11:21.160 align:middle line:84%
I don't think it's
really remote.

00:11:21.160 --> 00:11:23.180 align:middle line:84%
It's sort of like
tuning into a frequency.

00:11:23.180 --> 00:11:23.980 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Sure.

00:11:23.980 --> 00:11:24.780 align:middle line:90%
>>HEIN: Well.

00:11:24.780 --> 00:11:26.190 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: It's always out there.

00:11:26.190 --> 00:11:27.010 align:middle line:84%
>>HEIN: Yeah, it's
out there, and you're

00:11:27.010 --> 00:11:28.600 align:middle line:84%
deciding instead of
tuning into this room,

00:11:28.600 --> 00:11:30.225 align:middle line:84%
you're just tuning
into another signal.

00:11:30.225 --> 00:11:31.420 align:middle line:90%
So it's a type of resonance.

00:11:31.420 --> 00:11:33.212 align:middle line:84%
But the crop circles
kind of fit into that.

00:11:33.212 --> 00:11:36.430 align:middle line:84%
I did a few targets
on crop circles

00:11:36.430 --> 00:11:38.927 align:middle line:84%
when I was doing my initial
training back in the '90s,

00:11:38.927 --> 00:11:40.510 align:middle line:84%
and I didn't even
know what they were.

00:11:40.510 --> 00:11:42.780 align:middle line:84%
I got out of graduate school,
crop circle, never heard

00:11:42.780 --> 00:11:43.580 align:middle line:90%
of that word.

00:11:43.580 --> 00:11:46.240 align:middle line:84%
So I decided to go
over there with a guy

00:11:46.240 --> 00:11:48.760 align:middle line:84%
from around here who was giving
tours there, Ron Russell.

00:11:48.760 --> 00:11:49.910 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Over there
being Britain?

00:11:49.910 --> 00:11:51.040 align:middle line:90%
>>HEIN: Yeah, go over to the UK.

00:11:51.040 --> 00:11:52.665 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, I'm
going to finally get

00:11:52.665 --> 00:11:54.040 align:middle line:90%
some feedback on my target.

00:11:54.040 --> 00:11:57.860 align:middle line:84%
I was really shocked to see
these huge massive designs.

00:11:57.860 --> 00:11:59.860 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Were you in the
middle of these fields?

00:11:59.860 --> 00:12:00.660 align:middle line:90%
>>HEIN: Yeah.

00:12:00.660 --> 00:12:06.400 align:middle line:84%
The first one I ever went into
was by Silbury Hill in 1997.

00:12:06.400 --> 00:12:09.150 align:middle line:84%
And it was a fractal so-called
Coke snowflake, six-sided.

00:12:09.150 --> 00:12:10.600 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Yeah.

00:12:10.600 --> 00:12:12.970 align:middle line:84%
>>HEIN: That is what I had
studied in my dissertation

00:12:12.970 --> 00:12:15.140 align:middle line:90%
to look at fractal geometry .

00:12:15.140 --> 00:12:17.140 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, wow, that
can't be a coincidence.

00:12:17.140 --> 00:12:18.292 align:middle line:90%
I studied fractal geometry.

00:12:18.292 --> 00:12:20.000 align:middle line:84%
Here, I'm walking
around in one, but it's

00:12:20.000 --> 00:12:21.280 align:middle line:90%
the size of a football field.

00:12:21.280 --> 00:12:22.960 align:middle line:84%
When I studied them
in books, George,

00:12:22.960 --> 00:12:25.370 align:middle line:84%
they would save ink by
leaving the center blank.

00:12:25.370 --> 00:12:26.170 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Yeah.

00:12:26.170 --> 00:12:28.210 align:middle line:84%
>>HEIN: And here it
was, 300 feet across.

00:12:28.210 --> 00:12:29.060 align:middle line:90%
Really incredible.

00:12:29.060 --> 00:12:30.970 align:middle line:84%
And another thing
is, people were

00:12:30.970 --> 00:12:33.630 align:middle line:90%
experiencing really strange.

00:12:33.630 --> 00:12:34.430 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Feelings.

00:12:34.430 --> 00:12:35.370 align:middle line:90%
Energetic feelings.

00:12:35.370 --> 00:12:36.760 align:middle line:90%
>>HEIN: Feelings.

00:12:36.760 --> 00:12:37.720 align:middle line:90%
Energetic feelings.

00:12:37.720 --> 00:12:40.180 align:middle line:84%
And then you begin
to run into people

00:12:40.180 --> 00:12:43.050 align:middle line:84%
that have had their batteries
and cameras and other.

00:12:43.050 --> 00:12:44.050 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Drained, right?

00:12:44.050 --> 00:12:45.320 align:middle line:90%
>>HEIN: Drained, destroyed,

00:12:45.320 --> 00:12:46.120 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Yeah.

00:12:46.120 --> 00:12:49.862 align:middle line:84%
>>HEIN: Burnt out in
seconds of going into these.

00:12:49.862 --> 00:12:52.320 align:middle line:84%
And you begin to wonder what
in the world is going on here.

00:12:52.320 --> 00:12:54.340 align:middle line:84%
How these huge objects,
they have some sort

00:12:54.340 --> 00:12:56.570 align:middle line:90%
of energetic signature.

00:12:56.570 --> 00:12:58.570 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Didn't they also
investigate the crops?

00:12:58.570 --> 00:13:00.430 align:middle line:90%
Let's say it was a wheat field.

00:13:00.430 --> 00:13:03.880 align:middle line:84%
And they looked at the
chaff and the wheat

00:13:03.880 --> 00:13:06.760 align:middle line:84%
and there was something
genetically altered about it

00:13:06.760 --> 00:13:07.738 align:middle line:90%
or something like that?

00:13:07.738 --> 00:13:10.030 align:middle line:84%
>>HEIN: Well, I have to say,
a lot of the early science

00:13:10.030 --> 00:13:12.670 align:middle line:84%
in crop circles,
it's not entirely

00:13:12.670 --> 00:13:15.700 align:middle line:84%
clear what's causing some of
those effects that people saw.

00:13:15.700 --> 00:13:17.020 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: But they were effects.

00:13:17.020 --> 00:13:19.270 align:middle line:84%
>>HEIN: Yeah, there definitely
there are some effects.

00:13:19.270 --> 00:13:21.880 align:middle line:90%
You had changes in the plant.

00:13:21.880 --> 00:13:24.550 align:middle line:84%
Now, based on our research,
it's not clear to me

00:13:24.550 --> 00:13:27.130 align:middle line:84%
whether that is a
result of the energy

00:13:27.130 --> 00:13:29.080 align:middle line:90%
once the crop circle is there.

00:13:29.080 --> 00:13:31.337 align:middle line:84%
Because we did run into
people after a few years,

00:13:31.337 --> 00:13:33.670 align:middle line:84%
and I didn't think people,
initially people could do it.

00:13:33.670 --> 00:13:37.150 align:middle line:84%
I did run into people that
could actually make these,

00:13:37.150 --> 00:13:39.640 align:middle line:84%
not in 20 years' time, but
in maybe four or five hours

00:13:39.640 --> 00:13:41.272 align:middle line:84%
with a group of
five, six people.

00:13:41.272 --> 00:13:43.480 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: That could make it
the same as what you saw?

00:13:43.480 --> 00:13:44.290 align:middle line:90%
>>HEIN: Yeah, they could.

00:13:44.290 --> 00:13:45.090 align:middle line:90%
They really could.

00:13:45.090 --> 00:13:46.330 align:middle line:90%
And these were not hoaxers.

00:13:46.330 --> 00:13:49.060 align:middle line:84%
They were actually really
interested in the phenomena,

00:13:49.060 --> 00:13:50.560 align:middle line:84%
but they wanted to
interact with it.

00:13:50.560 --> 00:13:52.960 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: But somebody would
have seen them in the field.

00:13:52.960 --> 00:13:54.377 align:middle line:84%
>>HEIN: No, they
got good, George,

00:13:54.377 --> 00:13:57.692 align:middle line:84%
they got good doing
it in a very hidden.

00:13:57.692 --> 00:13:58.900 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: They do it at night?

00:13:58.900 --> 00:13:59.930 align:middle line:84%
>>HEIN: Yes, they
do it at night.

00:13:59.930 --> 00:14:00.940 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Flashlights?

00:14:00.940 --> 00:14:01.898 align:middle line:90%
>>HEIN: No flashlights.

00:14:01.898 --> 00:14:03.023 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: You're kidding me!

00:14:03.023 --> 00:14:05.487 align:middle line:84%
>>HEIN: I went out with them
a couple times just to prove,

00:14:05.487 --> 00:14:06.820 align:middle line:90%
I didn't think they could do it.

00:14:06.820 --> 00:14:08.860 align:middle line:84%
And they said, do you
want to see us make one?

00:14:08.860 --> 00:14:11.650 align:middle line:84%
And these were believers
that the crop circles

00:14:11.650 --> 00:14:13.090 align:middle line:90%
themselves have weird effects.

00:14:13.090 --> 00:14:15.540 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What do
these people believe?

00:14:15.540 --> 00:14:18.420 align:middle line:84%
>>HEIN: They believe that
there was some other original

00:14:18.420 --> 00:14:20.160 align:middle line:84%
phenomena, like
we're talking about,

00:14:20.160 --> 00:14:22.330 align:middle line:84%
that made ones that cannot
be easily explained.

00:14:22.330 --> 00:14:23.130 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: All right.

00:14:23.130 --> 00:14:24.600 align:middle line:84%
>>HEIN: They started
out by making,

00:14:24.600 --> 00:14:26.550 align:middle line:90%
to see, very small ones.

00:14:26.550 --> 00:14:27.842 align:middle line:90%
And they got bigger and bigger.

00:14:27.842 --> 00:14:29.383 align:middle line:84%
I said actually we
can make something

00:14:29.383 --> 00:14:30.360 align:middle line:90%
that looks half decent.

00:14:30.360 --> 00:14:32.375 align:middle line:84%
And we're getting these
weird effects ourselves

00:14:32.375 --> 00:14:33.750 align:middle line:84%
that people have
reported around,

00:14:33.750 --> 00:14:33.990 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Sure.

00:14:33.990 --> 00:14:35.490 align:middle line:84%
>>HEIN: These strange
electromagnetic effects.

00:14:35.490 --> 00:14:37.170 align:middle line:84%
Let's see if we can
change the pattern.

00:14:37.170 --> 00:14:42.510 align:middle line:84%
They became like
artists, science artists.

00:14:42.510 --> 00:14:44.310 align:middle line:84%
Changing the pattern,
seeing the effects,

00:14:44.310 --> 00:14:45.820 align:middle line:90%
seeing how people react.

00:14:45.820 --> 00:14:47.820 align:middle line:84%
So people did come
onto the scene

00:14:47.820 --> 00:14:49.830 align:middle line:84%
and end up making these
really large ones.

00:14:49.830 --> 00:14:52.600 align:middle line:84%
But, George, the main point is,
these large ones that they made

00:14:52.600 --> 00:14:53.400 align:middle line:90%
are also real.

00:14:53.400 --> 00:14:54.640 align:middle line:90%
I mean, at least electronically.

00:14:54.640 --> 00:14:55.510 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Absolutely.

00:14:55.510 --> 00:14:56.593 align:middle line:90%
>>HEIN: And energetically.

00:14:56.593 --> 00:14:59.580 align:middle line:84%
So I don't really see it
anymore as real versus man-made.

00:14:59.580 --> 00:15:03.435 align:middle line:84%
To me, they're all real, because
energetically, they have--.

00:15:03.435 --> 00:15:04.810 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Well,
you mentioned some

00:15:04.810 --> 00:15:06.910 align:middle line:84%
of the technical
failures of people who

00:15:06.910 --> 00:15:08.950 align:middle line:90%
are in these crop formations.

00:15:08.950 --> 00:15:10.850 align:middle line:90%
You take people on tours.

00:15:10.850 --> 00:15:11.650 align:middle line:90%
>>HEIN: Yes.

00:15:11.650 --> 00:15:13.770 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: All around the planet.

00:15:13.770 --> 00:15:15.520 align:middle line:84%
>>HEIN: One of the
main things that people

00:15:15.520 --> 00:15:18.910 align:middle line:84%
have seen over the years
in and around crop circles

00:15:18.910 --> 00:15:22.330 align:middle line:84%
that we have seen with our group
almost every year that we've

00:15:22.330 --> 00:15:27.880 align:middle line:84%
been there since the mid 1990s,
are weird and unexplained

00:15:27.880 --> 00:15:29.890 align:middle line:90%
camera and battery failures.

00:15:29.890 --> 00:15:31.750 align:middle line:84%
We saw it last year,
we saw the year before,

00:15:31.750 --> 00:15:34.180 align:middle line:84%
and we've just seen
it almost every time.

00:15:34.180 --> 00:15:36.640 align:middle line:84%
And I'd like you to
experience this for yourself,

00:15:36.640 --> 00:15:39.940 align:middle line:84%
because it really shows you
the power and the mystery

00:15:39.940 --> 00:15:41.783 align:middle line:84%
and the magic of
the crop circles.

00:15:41.783 --> 00:15:43.450 align:middle line:84%
Don't believe what
other people tell you

00:15:43.450 --> 00:15:46.010 align:middle line:84%
about the crop circles,
go see it for yourself.

00:15:46.010 --> 00:15:48.130 align:middle line:84%
And if you happen to be
one of the people who

00:15:48.130 --> 00:15:50.408 align:middle line:84%
has this experience
with the cameras

00:15:50.408 --> 00:15:52.950 align:middle line:84%
and the batteries like so many
other people have experienced,

00:15:52.950 --> 00:15:55.900 align:middle line:84%
including professional
film crews and so forth,

00:15:55.900 --> 00:15:57.700 align:middle line:84%
it'll be a story, an
experience that you

00:15:57.700 --> 00:16:00.860 align:middle line:84%
can talk about and tell people
about for a long, long time.

00:16:00.860 --> 00:16:04.030 align:middle line:84%
And it will be your personal
experience that shows you

00:16:04.030 --> 00:16:05.680 align:middle line:90%
that this is a real phenomena.

00:16:05.680 --> 00:16:08.470 align:middle line:84%
You don't need to listen
